01:11.572 --> 01:13.240
(alarm ringing)

01:14.575 --> 01:16.944
(groans)

01:16.944 --> 01:18.579
Damn.

01:19.813 --> 01:22.716
So we realize Nyla left her
history book in Kevin's car,

01:22.716 --> 01:24.618
then we had to drive all the
way over to the west side,

01:24.618 --> 01:27.688
but he already left Monica's
house by the time we got there.

01:27.688 --> 01:31.792
Long story short, it was quicker for her
to drop me off at the house, so she did.

01:31.792 --> 01:33.594
And that, O Mother,

01:33.594 --> 01:36.797
is the epically long, yet
tediously dull account of why my car

01:36.797 --> 01:37.932
isn't in the driveway.

01:37.932 --> 01:41.101
Ugh, well, just make sure
and pick it up after school.

01:41.101 --> 01:43.337
Because I have back to back
meetings. I can't drive you.

01:43.337 --> 01:44.905
(school bell ringing)

01:44.905 --> 01:47.141
A few questions, and feel free
to answer them in any order:

01:47.141 --> 01:48.976
How are you? And where's my car?

01:48.976 --> 01:51.278
Pretty good, and I have no idea.

01:51.278 --> 01:53.781
- Oh.
- You lost your car?

01:53.781 --> 01:55.749
I didn't lose it. It's just
currently occupying a space

01:55.749 --> 01:57.218
I'm presently unaware of.

01:57.218 --> 02:01.088
Well, let's see: You left the party,
you said you had to run a quick errand,

02:01.088 --> 02:02.623
and that you'd be right back.

02:02.623 --> 02:05.292
And you never came right back.

02:06.727 --> 02:08.329
I know.

02:08.329 --> 02:10.297
Maybe your car went to go find

02:10.297 --> 02:13.167
that hoodie you borrowed from me
last month that also went missing.

02:13.167 --> 02:14.735
Wow, mystery solved.

02:16.303 --> 02:17.838
Maddie, do you know what this is?

02:19.106 --> 02:21.041
Um, it's a bottle of water.

02:21.041 --> 02:22.710
Do the questions get harder...

02:27.014 --> 02:29.717
This... isn't water.

02:29.717 --> 02:31.852
No, it's not. It's vodka.

02:32.987 --> 02:34.688
We found this in Maddie's
locker this morning.

02:34.688 --> 02:37.591
And can you do that, just search my locker?

02:37.591 --> 02:38.659
Indeed, we can.

02:39.827 --> 02:41.862
One of my friends must have
put it in there as a joke.

02:41.862 --> 02:46.033
Alcohol on school premises is
a very serious offense, Maddie.

02:46.033 --> 02:47.101
It's cause for expulsion.

02:48.102 --> 02:50.571
Well, like I said, it's not mine.

02:50.571 --> 02:52.640
Good.

02:52.640 --> 02:53.941
Then this will just help clear it up.

02:55.142 --> 02:57.845
I just need you to blow on that tip.

03:00.681 --> 03:03.017
I don't have to do this. I know my rights.

03:05.919 --> 03:09.757
"Students who are suspected of consuming
illegal substances on school grounds

03:09.757 --> 03:11.825
will immediately be tested
by appointed school officials

03:11.825 --> 03:13.827
and will face possible expulsion.

03:13.827 --> 03:16.764
Any student refusing to submit to testing,

03:16.764 --> 03:19.266
will also face possible expulsion."

03:19.266 --> 03:20.701
Hm.

03:27.041 --> 03:28.642
(clears throat)

03:29.743 --> 03:31.078
(machine calibrates)

03:31.078 --> 03:32.246
Go ahead.

03:39.753 --> 03:41.188
- (beeping)
- Thank you.

03:49.797 --> 03:51.598
- Maddie, how could you?
- Mom.

03:51.598 --> 03:53.600
- This is so unfair.
- You better take this seriously.

03:53.600 --> 03:57.171
Unfortunately, I'm going to have
to report this to the Head Master,

03:57.171 --> 03:59.640
and it's his decision whether or
not Maddie can remain a student here.

03:59.640 --> 04:01.709
You've got to be kidding me.

04:01.709 --> 04:04.144
Is there any other option?

04:07.648 --> 04:09.116
24 hours of detox

04:09.116 --> 04:11.985
and 90 days at a sober-living
facility, effective immediately.

04:13.120 --> 04:14.888
The closest teen treatment center

04:14.888 --> 04:16.357
is 40 miles away, but...

04:16.357 --> 04:19.760
with parental consent, I
can arrange for you to live

04:19.760 --> 04:21.894
in an adult facility that's closer.

04:21.894 --> 04:23.597
You can go to school by day

04:23.597 --> 04:24.865
and spend your evenings getting sober,

04:24.865 --> 04:26.600
but, Maddie, I will be watching you...

04:26.600 --> 04:28.035
I'm not going to rehab.

04:28.035 --> 04:29.570
It's not rehab.

04:29.570 --> 04:32.706
It's a residential,
outpatient treatment facility.

04:35.642 --> 04:37.878
And you're out of your damn mind.

04:37.878 --> 04:39.913
(scoffs) I'm sorry to hear that.

04:42.049 --> 04:43.283
She'll do it.

04:45.052 --> 04:46.253
What?

04:51.291 --> 04:53.761
These are prohibited in detox.

04:53.761 --> 04:55.963
You can have it back after 24 hours.

04:55.963 --> 04:57.865
Now, please head down to room 248

04:57.865 --> 04:59.600
for the strip search.

