07:56.610 --> 07:57.978
I have good news.

07:57.978 --> 07:59.746
You're not dead.

08:00.847 --> 08:02.616
All right. Okay.

08:02.616 --> 08:05.252
We have a couple more of these,

08:05.252 --> 08:08.021
and then we are officially
done with the paperwork.

08:08.021 --> 08:11.024
That one is a statement that
Maddie has finished detox

08:11.024 --> 08:13.660
and is currently 24 hours
drug and alcohol free.

08:16.129 --> 08:18.865
So, Craig, how long have
you been a counselor here?

08:18.865 --> 08:21.568
Two years, yeah.

08:21.568 --> 08:23.704
And how long have you been sober?

08:23.704 --> 08:25.138
Hm?

08:25.138 --> 08:27.574
Me? Oh, no, no, no.

08:27.574 --> 08:31.078
I'm not in recovery. I'm just a counselor.

08:31.078 --> 08:33.013
You really got screwed
at the job fair, huh?

08:33.013 --> 08:34.581
- Maddie.
- What? He's like 12 years old.

08:34.581 --> 08:35.881
25.

08:35.881 --> 08:37.884
And highly certified.

08:37.884 --> 08:39.820
Would you like to see
my credentials, Maddie?

08:39.820 --> 08:41.655
That won't be necessary.

08:41.655 --> 08:44.625
Please excuse my daughter's rude behavior.

08:44.625 --> 08:46.860
Yes, I'm much more
affable when I'm not being

08:46.860 --> 08:48.829
institutionalized against my will.

08:48.829 --> 08:50.897
Right, now, this one says

08:50.897 --> 08:52.766
that if you go before the 90 days are up,

08:52.766 --> 08:55.669
I've still got to charge
your mom for all of it.

08:55.669 --> 08:57.604
So I can leave?

08:57.604 --> 09:00.040
No. No, you cannot.

09:00.040 --> 09:04.044
Now, all the information is in here.

09:04.044 --> 09:06.046
But...

09:09.016 --> 09:11.018
Thank you. But...

09:11.018 --> 09:13.620
Quick lowdown: group sessions, every day,

09:13.620 --> 09:14.921
one-on-ones with me, daily.

09:14.921 --> 09:17.758
You're on bathroom clean
up in the women's wing.

09:17.758 --> 09:19.226
Curfew is strictly enforced.

09:19.226 --> 09:22.629
And you will need to earn the
right to use your cell phone.

09:24.598 --> 09:25.866
You're joking.

09:25.866 --> 09:29.636
You do realize the withdrawal I'm going
to go through from not having my phone

09:29.636 --> 09:31.605
is far greater than what you're expecting

09:31.605 --> 09:33.173
from my so-called "addiction."

09:41.181 --> 09:43.750
Thank you. Also, for the first week,

09:43.750 --> 09:47.621
you can only leave for school
and scheduled group activities.

09:47.621 --> 09:49.656
But I get to go home on weekends, right?

09:51.224 --> 09:54.728
Recovery isn't a 9-5, Maddie. Okay?

09:56.063 --> 09:58.265
All right, okay. Look, here's...

09:59.266 --> 10:00.801
Here's the deal.

10:00.801 --> 10:03.670
You're going to find
temptation everywhere you go,

10:03.670 --> 10:06.339
which is why you're going to need
what I would call the four "S's."

10:06.339 --> 10:08.008
Now, that's sobriety...

10:08.008 --> 10:10.844
Cray-Cray, you need to get your ass
in the game room, like, right now.

10:10.844 --> 10:14.648
Oh right, yes. So everyone has
their own little nicknames for me.

10:14.648 --> 10:15.615
W... what's going on?

10:15.615 --> 10:17.184
Oh, Vern took the remote

10:17.184 --> 10:20.153
and said he's not giving it back until
he finds out who stole his Cheesy Chomps

10:20.153 --> 10:21.588
and they apologize.

10:21.588 --> 10:23.724
Okay, I will take care of that.

10:23.724 --> 10:25.926
Would you mind giving Maddie a quick tour?

10:25.926 --> 10:28.695
Not at all. Hi!

10:29.796 --> 10:30.831
(mouths)

10:30.831 --> 10:33.033
Well, I'll let you girls go ahead.

10:33.033 --> 10:34.668
I'm going to let myself out.

10:35.669 --> 10:37.604
You can call me if you need
me to bring you anything.

10:37.604 --> 10:38.739
- Okay?
- How?

10:38.739 --> 10:40.040
He took my friggin' phone.

10:40.040 --> 10:41.641
There's a house phone.

10:46.146 --> 10:47.814
(sighs) Hug me.

10:52.919 --> 10:55.222
You're so sweet. Come on, girl.

10:56.590 --> 10:58.592
Welcome to Springtime Meadows.

10:58.592 --> 11:00.260
You're gonna love it
here. We have so much fun.

11:00.260 --> 11:01.828
Sober people decorated the house.

11:01.828 --> 11:03.096
It's cool, right?

11:03.096 --> 11:05.665
All right, I'll give you a hint.
You're still very, very cold.

11:05.665 --> 11:07.868
Girl: All right, everybody, this is Maddie.

11:07.868 --> 11:09.102
Hi, Maddie. I'm Vern.

11:09.102 --> 11:10.871
Did anybody look in the piano?

11:10.871 --> 11:13.740
Maddie, you understand the difference
between right and wrong, right?

11:13.740 --> 11:15.742
If I did, would I be here?

11:15.742 --> 11:17.310
That's a good answer.

11:17.310 --> 11:19.146
Take this.

11:19.146 --> 11:20.680
Guard it with your life.

11:20.680 --> 11:22.282
Okay.

11:22.282 --> 11:24.651
- You're weird.
- You say that like it's a bad thing.

11:24.651 --> 11:27.220
All right, now, the
kitchen is straight ahead.

11:27.220 --> 11:28.889
The game room is to the
left, in the basement.

11:28.889 --> 11:30.257
That's where we play ping pong.

11:30.257 --> 11:32.826
I always win. I used to be
really good at all kinds of sports

11:32.826 --> 11:35.695
until I got into... Guess what
I go into. You'll never guess.

11:35.695 --> 11:38.598
For the sake of friends and
family, I hope it was downers.

11:38.598 --> 11:40.634
Meth. It was meth, girl.

11:40.634 --> 11:42.669
But you can't tell from my teeth, huh?

11:42.669 --> 11:44.571
I know, right? (Giggles)

11:44.571 --> 11:47.007
Girl: So yeah, it was really bad.
I lost custody of my daughter,

11:47.007 --> 11:49.943
but I'm gonna get her back. She's the
reason I gotta to get clean, you know.

11:49.943 --> 11:51.578
She's so sweet and so cute.

11:51.578 --> 11:53.180
Like, she-could-totally-be
in-pageants cute.

11:53.180 --> 11:56.349
I have her tattooed on my thigh. Not
her face, but her name. You want to see?

11:56.349 --> 11:58.718
- Maybe later.
- Well, you will see later, honey.

11:58.718 --> 12:00.987
Because guess what? We are...

12:00.987 --> 12:02.756
roomies!

12:02.756 --> 12:04.357
(shrieks)

12:04.357 --> 12:05.992
Oh, you don't know how excited I am.

12:05.992 --> 12:09.362
I've been waiting so long to have a
roommate that's not going through menopause.

12:09.362 --> 12:11.832
You know, you're crushing my will to live.

12:11.832 --> 12:14.367
Oh, sorry. Okay.

12:14.367 --> 12:17.571
So, you have to journal, because
it's a part of the program,

12:17.571 --> 12:19.706
but I love it because it's so much fun

12:19.706 --> 12:21.641
because I love to gossip.

12:21.641 --> 12:23.743
So, what are you in for?

12:23.743 --> 12:25.245
Um...

12:26.680 --> 12:28.648
a few sips of vodka.

12:28.648 --> 12:31.151
That's all? Girl, this is
going to be easy for you.

12:36.289 --> 12:38.091
What? You want some of
Vern's Cheesy Chomps?

12:39.292 --> 12:41.661
- I'm good.
- Okay.

12:41.661 --> 12:43.630
Trish? Trish, did you take my...

12:46.366 --> 12:47.801
Maddie Graham.

12:47.801 --> 12:48.969
Rebecca Granger.

12:52.138 --> 12:54.207
Well, I suppose it was
only a matter of time.

12:55.575 --> 12:57.043
Wait.

12:57.043 --> 12:58.211
So you two know each other?

12:58.211 --> 13:01.214
Yeah, we're old friends.

13:06.753 --> 13:07.954
Oh.

13:07.954 --> 13:09.990
- Oh my god.
- That's so nice.

13:14.728 --> 13:17.731
Last thing I remember is
drinking a lot of tequila.

13:19.299 --> 13:23.236
I woke up in lock up, them tell me me
stabbed my cheating husband four times.

13:25.605 --> 13:28.942
That guilt stays with me.

13:29.910 --> 13:32.212
Don't get me wrong, I hate him.

13:33.713 --> 13:35.081
But I hate me more.

13:37.050 --> 13:40.086
One time, the CIA

13:40.086 --> 13:42.789
dosed an entire village with LSD

13:42.789 --> 13:44.291
just to see what would happen.

13:44.291 --> 13:45.825
(laughing)

13:45.825 --> 13:47.727
Girl: They did.

13:47.727 --> 13:50.830
I guess what I've been
struggling with the most is...

13:50.830 --> 13:52.899
how my ugly past

13:52.899 --> 13:54.734
keeps coming back to haunt me.

14:01.975 --> 14:04.210
So, I had another dream last night.

14:05.946 --> 14:08.014
A relapse dream.

14:10.250 --> 14:12.585
And it's that guilt you wake up with.

14:14.688 --> 14:16.256
It's hard to shake.

14:18.325 --> 14:21.695
Even when you wake up and you
realize you were just dreaming,

14:21.695 --> 14:23.229
you didn't do anything wrong...

14:24.698 --> 14:26.099
and I...

14:27.100 --> 14:28.702
I just...

14:31.805 --> 14:33.640
I don't really want to
talk about this right now.

14:40.347 --> 14:42.349
We'll deal with this at your
one-on-one tomorrow, okay?

14:42.349 --> 14:43.850
- Okay, thank you.
- All right.

14:45.719 --> 14:48.021
(sighs) Okay, well, my friends,

14:48.021 --> 14:52.021
today is a day of hellos and goodbyes.

14:52.892 --> 14:55.362
Maddie, would you like
to introduce yourself?

14:56.763 --> 14:58.598
Hi, I'm Maddie.

14:58.598 --> 15:02.268
Oh right, yes. So in group, we
introduce ourselves by saying,

15:02.268 --> 15:05.839
"Hi, I'm whomever, and I'm an alcoholic."

15:08.041 --> 15:10.677
Hi, I'm whomever, and I'm an alcoholic.

15:10.677 --> 15:14.347
Very good, very good. I
haven't heard that one before.

15:16.082 --> 15:17.884
I'm sorry, guys. I just don't belong here.

15:17.884 --> 15:19.185
You know?

15:19.185 --> 15:20.754
I really don't.

15:20.754 --> 15:23.690
I appreciate your sobriety journey,

15:23.690 --> 15:25.759
but I'm just here because I have to be.

15:26.659 --> 15:29.029
Craig, I just remembered something.

15:29.029 --> 15:30.663
- I don't belong here either.
- Me either.

15:30.663 --> 15:32.332
(all laughing)

15:33.900 --> 15:37.604
Did anyone else feel like they
didn't belong here their first day?

15:37.604 --> 15:40.006
- (overlapping agreement)
- Yeah, I thought so.

15:41.007 --> 15:43.676
Maddie, no one thinks they belong here...

15:44.711 --> 15:46.346
at first, but...

15:46.346 --> 15:50.250
I think that where it took
some of these guys weeks

15:50.250 --> 15:51.985
to come around,

15:51.985 --> 15:54.621
I've got a feeling that it's
going to take you two days.

15:56.756 --> 15:59.793
Two days of hating me,

15:59.793 --> 16:01.628
hating them, hating this place.

16:03.129 --> 16:04.631
But I do have faith in you.

16:07.100 --> 16:08.835
He said the same thing to all of us.

16:08.835 --> 16:11.604
- (laughing)
- I absolutely did not.

16:11.604 --> 16:13.673
- Sorry, brother.
- All right, okay.

16:13.673 --> 16:15.341
Maddie, hello.

16:15.341 --> 16:18.711
- (overlapping greetings)
- Hello, kid.

16:18.711 --> 16:19.913
(under breath) Hi, Maddie.

16:19.913 --> 16:23.316
And we are bidding a very fond farewell

16:23.316 --> 16:25.285
to our very dear Douglas,

16:25.285 --> 16:27.687
AKA Mr. "I'm going to rip your head off."

16:27.687 --> 16:29.689
We're really going to miss you, buddy.

16:30.857 --> 16:32.725
As is Springtime Meadows' ritual,

16:32.725 --> 16:34.694
we have a parting gift for you,

16:34.694 --> 16:37.297
and, Doug, you will leave
behind something for the house.

16:37.297 --> 16:38.698
Great.

16:40.300 --> 16:44.300
Okay, so, we all chipped
in and we got you this.

16:48.241 --> 16:50.877
Oh, you replaced the one I lost.

16:50.877 --> 16:53.613
(laughing)

16:53.613 --> 16:55.348
Man: Put it on. Put it on.

16:55.348 --> 16:56.883
Man: Yes.

16:56.883 --> 16:59.719
- (cheering)
- Handsome!

16:59.719 --> 17:01.788
Trish: Don't lose this one.

17:03.156 --> 17:05.625
Wow. (Clears throat)

17:05.625 --> 17:07.861
Um...

17:07.861 --> 17:10.964
I'm just really grateful for you all...

17:12.065 --> 17:14.666
and for this house,

17:14.666 --> 17:15.935
and for my sobriety.

17:18.570 --> 17:21.974
My life is so different now, and I'm just
so excited to go out there and live it.

17:23.810 --> 17:26.945
So I made something for the house.

17:26.945 --> 17:29.682
It's kind of stupid, but...

17:35.755 --> 17:38.925
That's beautiful. You made this?

17:38.925 --> 17:42.128
- Yeah.
- Aw, thank you.

17:42.128 --> 17:44.063
All right, come on, everyone.

17:44.063 --> 17:45.765
- Bring it in.
- Watch my vase.

17:45.765 --> 17:47.367
Craig: Yeah, watch the vase.

17:48.801 --> 17:51.704
Hey, you take care of these guys, okay?

17:52.705 --> 17:54.240
And let them take care of you.

17:55.742 --> 17:57.143
- Okay?
- Okay.

17:58.311 --> 18:00.113
(chattering)

18:02.315 --> 18:04.017
Welcome to the fun house.

18:24.137 --> 18:25.905
Ooh, this is pretty.

18:25.905 --> 18:27.607
My dad gave that to me. He's dead.

18:29.108 --> 18:30.643
Oh, I'm sorry.

18:31.644 --> 18:32.912
Sorry.

18:32.912 --> 18:35.782
It plays the theme from Ice Castles.

18:35.782 --> 18:37.884
I don't know what that is.

18:37.884 --> 18:40.954
So when did your dad...

18:40.954 --> 18:43.756
Three years ago, this Memorial Day.

18:43.756 --> 18:45.625
And how old were you?

18:45.625 --> 18:46.960
14.

18:46.960 --> 18:49.195
Well, that sucks.

18:49.195 --> 18:50.663
I'm so sorry.

18:54.667 --> 18:57.704
So how did he die?

18:57.704 --> 18:59.639
He was killed by a drunk driver.

19:00.840 --> 19:02.675
The irony is not lost on me.

19:02.675 --> 19:03.576
Huh?

19:04.744 --> 19:06.145
Never mind.

19:50.757 --> 19:52.091
Dad?

19:52.091 --> 19:54.294
Hi, princess.

19:54.294 --> 19:56.663
You know I hate it when you call me that.

19:57.664 --> 19:58.731
I know.

20:01.901 --> 20:03.336
I miss you.

20:04.570 --> 20:05.672
Like, a lot.

20:05.672 --> 20:07.707
Shh.

20:07.707 --> 20:10.610
I'm sure I'm going to be
seeing you very, very soon.

20:10.610 --> 20:13.246
- (horn blaring)
- (gasps)

20:13.246 --> 20:15.081
(breathing heavily)

20:25.124 --> 20:28.161
Tell me again why I'm not
allowed to drive myself to school?

20:28.161 --> 20:30.330
I hate to be the bearer
of bad tidings, Maddie,

20:30.330 --> 20:32.198
but you're going to be
under constant supervision.

20:32.198 --> 20:35.001
Well, good. You'll get to see that
my life is actually pretty boring,

20:35.001 --> 20:36.936
and I'm not an addict.

20:36.936 --> 20:39.772
Have you ever stopped to consider
the reason I was drinking in school

20:39.772 --> 20:41.774
is because it's insufferably boring?

20:41.774 --> 20:44.577
I make decent grades. How
do you think that's possible?

20:44.577 --> 20:47.080
- Maybe we should just open up a bar on campus
- Maybe you should.

20:47.080 --> 20:48.281
I'll get right on that.

20:55.688 --> 20:56.789
Are you taking drugs?

20:57.790 --> 20:59.125
Yes, I do crack.

20:59.125 --> 21:01.728
Lots and lots of crack. In
fact, I'm on crack right now.

21:01.728 --> 21:03.329
I'm serious, Maddie.

21:03.329 --> 21:04.664
Do you do drugs?

21:04.664 --> 21:06.366
(dance music playing)

21:11.704 --> 21:13.172
No, I do not do drugs.

21:14.607 --> 21:16.776
But even if I did, what
business is it of yours?

21:16.776 --> 21:19.612
Aren't you supposed to be getting kids
into college and handing out condoms?

21:19.612 --> 21:23.149
I'm just not exactly sure why
you've taken such an interest in me.

21:23.149 --> 21:27.086
I'm a good student. Hell, I'm
a frickin' virgin, by choice.

21:27.086 --> 21:28.888
Ask anyone.

21:28.888 --> 21:30.256
So whatever you think you know...

21:30.256 --> 21:34.327
Maddie, a lot of aggression comes
out in the early stages of recovery.

21:34.327 --> 21:36.929
While it makes sense that
you would take it out on me,

21:36.929 --> 21:39.599
the deal I made with
you was more than fair.

21:39.599 --> 21:43.599
So I'm here, when you're ready
to have a real conversation.

21:44.036 --> 21:47.607
But until then, I hope
you like Christian pop.

21:47.607 --> 21:49.041
(Christian pop playing)

21:49.041 --> 21:51.711
