21:51.711 --> 21:55.114
â™ª Savior â™ª

21:55.114 --> 21:57.016
I love that song.

21:57.016 --> 21:59.919
Oh, that was the longest
car ride of my life.

22:01.921 --> 22:03.689
- Let me know if you need anything.
- I don't.

22:06.025 --> 22:07.894
Hey, babe.

22:07.894 --> 22:10.930
Why did you come to school
with the guidance counselor?

22:12.632 --> 22:14.867
Uh, my car is in the shop.

22:14.867 --> 22:18.704
And Ms. Molina lives close to us, and her
and my mom are friends, and I hate her.

22:18.704 --> 22:20.640
I would have given you a ride.

22:21.707 --> 22:23.709
Oh, my phone's broken.

22:23.709 --> 22:25.645
And as much as I love you,

22:25.645 --> 22:28.614
(clears throat) I'm a terrible girlfriend

22:28.614 --> 22:30.583
because I don't have your number memorized.

22:30.583 --> 22:32.752
My life is falling apart. Hold me.

22:34.954 --> 22:37.323
- Come here, babe.
- Okay.

22:39.926 --> 22:41.661
(giggles)

22:42.662 --> 22:44.297
I mean, here's the thing.

22:44.297 --> 22:47.166
I've always been the kind of person
that's like, "Sure, whatever."

22:47.166 --> 22:48.835
I kind of just go with the flow,

22:48.835 --> 22:51.103
because life is so short, right?

22:52.271 --> 22:55.741
Wait, what was I talking about? (Laughs)

22:57.610 --> 22:59.912
Have you ever told a little white lie...

23:00.980 --> 23:04.217
and had to pile on many
other little white lies

23:04.217 --> 23:06.986
to hide that little white lie?

23:08.187 --> 23:10.022
I have never told a lie in my entire life.

23:10.022 --> 23:11.624
Seriously?

23:11.624 --> 23:13.793
See how good I am at it?

23:13.793 --> 23:15.161
- Mm.
- (laughs)

23:16.162 --> 23:18.798
If Zack asks, my car is in the shop.

23:19.966 --> 23:21.934
- Oh, little white lie?
- Mm-hmm.

23:23.669 --> 23:25.238
Where is your car?

23:25.238 --> 23:27.006
Duh, it's where I left it.

23:27.006 --> 23:28.341
Where'd you leave it?

23:30.643 --> 23:31.844
Beats the hell out of me.

23:34.347 --> 23:35.681
Is your backpack in your car?

23:35.681 --> 23:38.584
- Yeah, why?
- Is your computer in your backpack?

23:38.584 --> 23:39.919
Mm-hmm.

23:41.687 --> 23:43.222
(at same time) Find my device.

23:43.222 --> 23:47.222
Oh, I am dazzled by your insanely
clever problem-solving skills.

23:48.060 --> 23:51.197
Yeah, they're nothing
compared to my breasts.

23:51.197 --> 23:52.732
(clears throat)

23:52.732 --> 23:54.634
- Yeah, they're so spectacular.
- (laughs)

23:55.601 --> 23:57.637
(music playing over radio)

24:01.941 --> 24:03.576
(Wes humming)

24:04.610 --> 24:06.045
I'm sorry.

24:06.045 --> 24:08.281
Maddie: No, it's cool. I'm almost done.

24:12.818 --> 24:16.622
"There is a wisdom that is woe,
but there is a woe that is madness."

24:16.622 --> 24:17.657
Huh?

24:18.658 --> 24:19.892
The book.

24:24.730 --> 24:26.165
Look, I have to get out of here.

24:26.165 --> 24:28.801
I need to get some nail
polish. Do you want to come?

24:30.636 --> 24:32.038
Um, it's after curfew.

24:32.038 --> 24:33.739
- So...
- Hm.

24:36.976 --> 24:39.145
Do I look like a girl who obeys curfews?

24:40.313 --> 24:43.149
Well, I guess you wouldn't
be in here if you did, huh?

24:43.149 --> 24:44.717
Mm-mm.

24:46.719 --> 24:50.323
(clears throat) Look, I'm
climbing the walls here,

24:50.323 --> 24:53.826
so I don't care where
we go, I just need to go.

24:54.827 --> 24:55.962
Anywhere.

24:57.763 --> 25:01.567
I'm a little all over the place, so you
can come or not. Just don't tell, okay?

25:04.570 --> 25:06.772
There's a hole in the back fence.
We'd have to crawl through it.

25:11.043 --> 25:12.912
- You really want to do this?
- Mm-hmm.

25:18.150 --> 25:19.652
You're gonna be trouble.

25:26.158 --> 25:28.194
So what's the deal with you and Rebecca?

25:28.194 --> 25:30.763
Ugh, we used to be best friends.

25:30.763 --> 25:34.300
It's all very "teen girl
drama-rama." Too angsty to get into.

25:34.300 --> 25:36.702
Fair enough. We should probably get back.

25:37.737 --> 25:40.806
You've obviously never been
shopping with a girl before.

25:40.806 --> 25:41.907
Obviously not.

25:41.907 --> 25:46.212
So, how did you end up at
good old Sunshine Valley,

25:46.212 --> 25:48.280
or Springtime Mausoleum.
Whatever it's called.

25:49.281 --> 25:50.683
Which time?

25:51.784 --> 25:54.620
Oh, it's too angsty to go into.

25:55.621 --> 25:56.989
TouchÃƒÂ©.

25:58.157 --> 26:00.893
We should stick to the basics.
What's your favorite color?

26:00.893 --> 26:02.662
What's your lucky number?

26:02.662 --> 26:04.330
What do you want to be when you grow up?

26:04.330 --> 26:08.330
(laughs) Blood red, 24,

26:08.734 --> 26:10.002
mortician.

26:11.203 --> 26:13.839
- Seriously?
- True story.

26:13.839 --> 26:17.009
The first funeral I ever
went to was my dad's.

26:18.044 --> 26:19.645
Wes: I'm sorry.

26:19.645 --> 26:23.749
The funeral directors were
really nice and caring.

26:23.749 --> 26:26.185
They made something so unbearable,

26:26.185 --> 26:28.220
not exactly bearable, but less bad.

26:29.221 --> 26:31.724
That's what I want to do too,

26:31.724 --> 26:33.225
make things a little less bad for people.

26:35.861 --> 26:39.265
I'm sorry, I've never
told anyone that before,

26:39.265 --> 26:41.634
and that is creepy and morbid.

26:41.634 --> 26:43.202
It's not.

26:44.737 --> 26:45.905
It's really not.

26:47.673 --> 26:49.341
What do you think?

26:49.341 --> 26:51.844
- Come on, eh?
- Smile, you're on camera.

26:51.844 --> 26:53.212
Oh yeah.

26:57.149 --> 26:59.719
- (cans opening)
- (choral music)

27:01.587 --> 27:04.023
Come on. It's kind of funny.

27:04.023 --> 27:05.658
Right?

27:07.293 --> 27:09.228
Yeah, I'll see you outside.

27:16.268 --> 27:19.105
Whoa, hold up there, hoss.

27:19.105 --> 27:20.573
Look what I got us.

27:22.775 --> 27:24.643
Ta-da.

27:24.643 --> 27:28.914
Courtesy of Jocelyn Berman's
slightly older sister, Eloise,

27:28.914 --> 27:30.282
who kind of looks like me but...

27:30.282 --> 27:31.317
You're kidding me, right?

27:31.317 --> 27:33.719
- What?
- I'm committed to my recovery this time.

27:33.719 --> 27:35.321
- Why the hell do you think I'm here?
- Okay.

27:35.321 --> 27:37.189
Never mind.

27:39.024 --> 27:40.693
It's a joke.

27:40.693 --> 27:43.362
Look. Look, I'm getting rid of it.

27:43.362 --> 27:45.765
All right? Look.

27:46.699 --> 27:48.367
I'm sorry. I'm a jerk.

27:53.706 --> 27:57.576
Thank you for saving me from the
evil forces of the drug store.

28:00.045 --> 28:01.180
No worries.

28:01.180 --> 28:02.715
(tires screech)

28:12.258 --> 28:13.759
Okay.

28:20.266 --> 28:21.734
Well, this is bad.

28:22.735 --> 28:24.603
I think you've just set
a record, breaking rules

28:24.603 --> 28:25.604
on your second night here, Maddie.

28:25.604 --> 28:28.874
Just don't kick him out. It was my idea.

28:28.874 --> 28:30.176
He was just protecting me.

28:30.176 --> 28:31.977
Okay.

28:31.977 --> 28:33.946
Okay, Maddie, why don't you
go upstairs, pack your bags,

28:33.946 --> 28:35.581
and I'll call your mom to come pick you up.

28:35.581 --> 28:38.317
Ms. Molina can make arrangements
for your expulsion from Parsons-Bell.

28:38.317 --> 28:40.352
- You can't do...
- Neither of us is leaving.

28:42.688 --> 28:43.656
Right, Craig?

28:57.670 --> 28:59.872
I need you to pee in this cup.

28:59.872 --> 29:01.273
Okay, Maddie?

29:01.273 --> 29:03.142
And this is going to be your only warning.

29:03.142 --> 29:04.143
Do you hear me?

29:05.144 --> 29:07.613
- Yeah.
- Go on, go.

29:07.613 --> 29:08.747
Go.

29:11.717 --> 29:12.651
Where do you think you're going?

29:15.221 --> 29:16.989
Not good, Maddie.

29:16.989 --> 29:20.125
Wes is my sponsee. I can't have
him participating in reckless...

29:20.125 --> 29:21.694
I know, I messed up.

29:21.694 --> 29:22.628
He...

29:23.762 --> 29:25.364
You'll get the hang of this, okay?

29:25.364 --> 29:26.632
It's like riding a bike.

29:26.632 --> 29:28.100
I don't know how to ride a bike.

29:28.100 --> 29:29.235
What?

29:29.235 --> 29:32.238
I fell off the first time I tried,
and it just seemed easier to walk.

29:32.238 --> 29:34.707
And your parents didn't
make you get back on?

29:34.707 --> 29:35.808
Workaholics.

29:35.808 --> 29:38.577
Okay, well, I'm going to teach you.

29:38.577 --> 29:41.247
I didn't always look like this,
you know. I used to be a dancer.

29:42.248 --> 29:43.349
Hmm.

29:45.918 --> 29:47.753
Wow.

29:47.753 --> 29:49.855
- Dude, you were hot.
- I'm still hot.

29:52.691 --> 29:54.593
You don't even know me.

29:54.593 --> 29:55.728
Why do you care?

29:57.029 --> 30:00.299
One day, you're going to have a
moment like this with someone else,

30:00.299 --> 30:02.201
sharing your experience.

30:02.201 --> 30:04.770
That's how it works.

30:04.770 --> 30:06.005
And it does work.

30:19.285 --> 30:20.586
Yeah!

30:20.586 --> 30:22.187
Yeah.

30:29.662 --> 30:31.030
Wes, you bailed me out once.

30:33.599 --> 30:34.733
Now, I've returned that favor.

30:37.569 --> 30:40.239
Are you sure you want to use that
get-out-of-jail-free card on this girl?

30:42.942 --> 30:44.143
Yeah.

30:45.110 --> 30:46.245
I'm worried.

30:46.245 --> 30:49.214
- Don't be.
- I can tell you like her, Wes.

30:49.214 --> 30:52.084
And that means you are potentially
putting your sobriety at risk,

30:52.084 --> 30:53.285
as well as Maddie's.

30:54.653 --> 30:56.689
I think you're overreacting.

30:56.689 --> 30:58.357
No.

30:58.357 --> 30:59.725
You told me

30:59.725 --> 31:02.661
that you were going to follow
every part of the program this time.

31:02.661 --> 31:04.830
And that means no dating the first year.

31:04.830 --> 31:08.167
- I'm not dating her man.
- It's the only way that your recovery

31:08.167 --> 31:09.702
is going to take top priority.

31:11.870 --> 31:13.639
So you and Maddie can't happen.

31:15.641 --> 31:16.575
We clear?

31:17.743 --> 31:19.611
Yeah.

31:19.611 --> 31:21.080
We're clear.

31:28.354 --> 31:29.955
(door closes)

31:33.092 --> 31:34.994
- Hey, sorry about last night.
- Oh, don't worry about it.

31:34.994 --> 31:38.230
- How did you even manage...
- I can't really talk right now.

31:38.230 --> 31:39.631
I have to go. I'm sorry.

31:39.631 --> 31:41.233
Sorry.

31:50.109 --> 31:51.310
Found it.

31:52.578 --> 31:55.681
I'm gonna give you a
free pass on explaining

31:55.681 --> 31:57.816
why your car was parked
on the west side of town

31:57.816 --> 31:59.718
or how you got home.

31:59.718 --> 32:01.253
Thanks.

32:03.822 --> 32:05.357
How's the...

32:06.658 --> 32:08.127
How are you?

32:08.127 --> 32:10.729
Um... (clears throat)

32:13.632 --> 32:16.101
"Damp and drizzly."

32:23.609 --> 32:25.611
You're gonna get through this.

32:25.611 --> 32:27.679
We're gonna get through this.

32:32.618 --> 32:33.952
I...

32:35.788 --> 32:39.858
found this on the front seat of your car.

32:42.061 --> 32:44.763
I'm glad that you and Zack are being safe.

32:49.835 --> 32:52.938
Yeah. Right.

32:52.938 --> 32:55.040
You know, Maddie, you can talk to me...

32:55.040 --> 32:56.642
I have to go.

32:56.642 --> 32:59.078
Um...

32:59.078 --> 33:01.013
I have things to do inside.

33:01.013 --> 33:03.082
So, I'll see you later.

33:10.756 --> 33:12.925
Trish: Come on, Maddie. We're
going to be late for the AA meeting.

33:13.959 --> 33:15.127
- (Maddie crying)
- Trish: Maddie?

33:15.127 --> 33:16.161
No, I'm fine.

33:16.161 --> 33:17.930
Please, no.

33:17.930 --> 33:19.698
No, what happened?

33:21.633 --> 33:22.835
(crying) I don't know.

33:25.604 --> 33:28.574
This... this was in my car.

33:30.175 --> 33:32.744
I don't... I don't remember.

33:33.912 --> 33:36.348
I don't remember what
happened on Thursday night.

33:37.616 --> 33:38.951
And I've never...

33:39.985 --> 33:42.121
(crying) I've never had sex before.

33:43.655 --> 33:46.191
And if I did, it wasn't with my boyfriend,

33:46.191 --> 33:50.191
because he was babysitting
his brother on Thursday.

33:52.064 --> 33:53.765
(sobbing)

33:53.765 --> 33:57.169
What if I cheated on
Zack with some stranger?

34:00.772 --> 34:03.175
Maddie, if you were too drunk to remember,

34:03.175 --> 34:04.576
then it wasn't consensual.

34:04.576 --> 34:05.911
But that's the thing.

34:05.911 --> 34:07.613
What if I initiated it?

34:10.649 --> 34:12.050
(sobbing)

34:12.050 --> 34:13.685
What if I was...

34:14.953 --> 34:17.623
(voice breaking) What if I was raped?

34:17.623 --> 34:19.591
I don't know!

34:19.591 --> 34:21.025
I can't remember.

34:21.025 --> 34:22.694
What if this wasn't the first time?

34:24.163 --> 34:26.130
(crying continues)

34:26.130 --> 34:28.800
I don't know. I can't remember.

34:28.800 --> 34:32.170
- Maddie. It's okay, it's okay.
- (crying heavily)

34:33.237 --> 34:34.973
It's okay.

34:36.241 --> 34:37.775
(sobbing heavily)

34:39.978 --> 34:41.213
(people chatting)

34:41.213 --> 34:42.947
Just mingle, ya hear, Maddie?

34:42.947 --> 34:44.315
Mmm, yeah.

34:45.717 --> 34:48.187
- Hey, how you doing?
- Hi!

34:58.130 --> 35:01.166
Maddie, there's somebody that
I really want you to meet.

35:01.166 --> 35:03.202
Okay, I think you're going to love her.

35:03.202 --> 35:04.703
Her and I have been best friends forever,

35:04.703 --> 35:07.706
and she has really been through it.

35:07.706 --> 35:10.909
But she's so sweet, and I really think
that maybe you could open up to her

35:10.909 --> 35:12.711
more than you could with Wiener Dog.

35:12.711 --> 35:14.012
That's my nickname for Craig.

35:14.012 --> 35:15.147
(laughs)

35:18.617 --> 35:20.686
I'm Cynthia.

35:20.686 --> 35:21.620
Nice to meet you.

35:30.028 --> 35:31.997
- I can't believe you.
- Maddie, I understand you're upset.

35:31.997 --> 35:33.799
Don't you think it's a
little hypocritical of you

35:33.799 --> 35:35.334
to call me out when you're an addict too?

35:36.768 --> 35:38.337
Did you hear what you just did?

35:38.337 --> 35:39.905
- Called you out.
- Nope.

35:39.905 --> 35:43.575
You just admitted you were an addict,
albeit accidentally, but it still counts.

35:43.575 --> 35:44.910
Whatever.

35:44.910 --> 35:47.107
- I'm 12 years sober, Maddie...
- And this is something

35:47.108 --> 35:48.108
you could have brought up many times.

35:48.146 --> 35:50.749
The program works because of its anonymity.

35:50.749 --> 35:54.286
Fine, but if one person
finds out about my situation,

35:54.286 --> 35:55.621
Cynthia,

35:55.621 --> 35:58.657
believe you me, the entire
school will find out about yours.

36:02.794 --> 36:04.196
(sighs)

36:11.003 --> 36:12.704
Hey, it's me. Are you home?

36:14.640 --> 36:16.241
How is she?

36:16.241 --> 36:18.176
She's fine.

36:18.176 --> 36:19.878
Pissed at me.

36:19.878 --> 36:22.047
But I expected she would be.

36:22.047 --> 36:25.083
- She's going to be okay though.
- Voilà.

36:26.118 --> 36:27.986
Oh wow.

36:27.986 --> 36:30.689
I cleaned her room today.
This is what I found.

36:32.291 --> 36:34.626
I didn't realize it had gotten this bad.

36:35.994 --> 36:37.596
How could I not have known?

36:41.099 --> 36:42.734
Jamie would have known.

36:44.269 --> 36:46.305
He always knew what was going on with her.

36:46.305 --> 36:48.106
It's like he had this sixth sense.

36:49.308 --> 36:50.842
(sighs)

36:50.842 --> 36:52.811
First time she had a crush
on a boy, he called it.

36:54.046 --> 36:56.782
The first time she smoked pot,
he was the one who busted her.

36:59.584 --> 37:00.719
They got each other.

